ooking into how resources are loaded in a Gradle setup. If there's no XML default, I might need to make two calls. I wonder about the ClassLoader context being null; it looks like it shouldn't be an issue. Maybe I should check if native image resources can include test resources automatically. Adding `src/test/resources` could help since that might be included in the test classpath. Let me dig deeper into this!\\\"},{\\\"type\\\":\\\"summary_text\\\",\\\"text\\\":\\\"**Considering project complexity**\\\\n\\\\nI'm thinking that while more real might be an option, it also introduces more complexity. I need to check the existing import styles to see if static is used below. Okay, maybe I should adjust the build, but wait—no, perhaps the package name is already set up in the directory. I just need to focus on using the write function appropriately. It feels like there's a lot to consider!\\\"}]}\"}, {\"type\": \"toolCall\", \"id\": \"call_qUBbsmdgxhAmT8rezIDWvg1q|fc_00df4d6207ce823e0169fdb1b7b5ec81a3a131fbad0d71d01f\", \"name\": \"write\", \"arguments\": {\"path\": \"tests/src/org.jboss.arquillian.config/arquillian-config-impl-base/1.1.10.Final/src/test/java/org_jboss_arquillian_config/arquillian_config_impl_base/FileUtilsTest.java\", \"content\": \"/*\\n * Copyright and related rights waived via CC0\\n *\\n * You should have received a copy of the CC0 legalcode along with this\\n * work. If not, see <http://creativecommons.org/publicdomain/zero/1.0/>.\\n */\\npackage org_jboss_arquillian_config.arquillian_config_impl_base;\\n\\nimport org.jboss.arquillian.config.impl.extension.ConfigurationRegistrar;\\nimport org.jboss.arquillian.core.api.event.ManagerStarted;\\nimport org.junit.jupiter.api.Test;\\n\\nimport static org.assertj.core.api.Assertions.assertThat;\\nimport static org.assertj.core.api.Assertions.assertThatThrownBy;\\n\\npublic class FileUtilsTest {\\n    private static final String PROPERTIES_RESOURCE = \\\"file-utils-test-arquillian.properties\\\";\\n\\n   